<p class="x_MsoNormal"><%= image_tag(attachments['msa.jpg'].url, style:"display: block;", align:"left",height:"413", hspace:"12", width:"308") -%><b><span style="font-size:11.0pt; font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">Mr. Mani Shankar Aiyar</span></b><span style="font-size:11.0pt; font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"> is an ex-Diplomat turned politician. He spent 26 distinguished years in the IFS, the last 5 of which were spent in deputation to the Prime Minister’s Office under <b>Rajiv Gandhi</b>. In 1989, he resigned from the Civil Service to take up a career in politics. He was first elected to the Lok Sabha in 1991 and has since also been a Cabinet Minister in the 2004 UPA Government. He has served as the Head of the ministry overseeing the <b>Panchayati Raj</b>. He has also held the portfolios for <b>Minister of Petroleum and Natural Gas, Youth Affairs and Sports and Development of North Eastern Region</b>. In March 2010, he was nominated to the Rajya Sabha by the President for his expertise in the field of Social Service. An accomplished author and columnist, his publications include <i>Remembering Rajiv</i> (1992) and <em><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">Confessions of a Secular Fundamentalist</span></em> (2004) amongst others.</span></p>
